					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you're coding for an emulator, you might as well target TurboGrafx-16 instead of NES + MMC5. Mednafen runs both.<br /><br />To me, the &quot;role-playing&quot; with discrete mappers and size limits is mostly important for getting your game into a community multicart. But then again, it might be a spectrum:<br /><br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Multicart release eligible (discrete; 128K or smaller depending on submission rules)</li><li>Solo cart release eligible (discrete, MMC1, MMC3, FME-7; biggest memory mapper accepts)</li><li>Emulation eligible (VRC6, Namco 163, MMC5, and other obscure mappers; biggest memory mapper accepts)</li><li>The next more powerful system (TG16)</li><li>Screw it, I'm making a PC game (<em>Alwa</em>, <em>Shovel Knight</em>)</li></ol></div>

